    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>162</ID>
      <DefaultText>You take two steps toward the cage, but the moment you reach your hand toward it, the Chimaera stops you with a bark. "What do you think you're doing? Your mission is a failure. The last thing I want is to have you out there making more trouble for me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>163</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Where is Mazzof? I need to speak with him."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>164</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I want to speak with Mazzof about that artifact I found."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>165</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>166</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Where are you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>167</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're not in the Chimaera's hideout. Where is that place?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>168</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>169</ID>
      <DefaultText>He spreads his arms in mock welcome. "I'm on a gods-damned beach having the time of my life. Where's it look like I am?"

He crosses his arms across his chest. "What the hells did you want?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>170</ID>
      <DefaultText>He only glares in response.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>171</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Are you really Mazzof? The one who talks to machines?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>172</ID>
      <DefaultText>His brow furrows, while his artificial eye socket cycles through about a dozen different eye patterns in two seconds. His tone drops to a dangerous low. "Who are you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>173</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And where's our beloved leader?" The way he says 'beloved leader' leads you to believe he's anything but. "I can't believe you'd be allowed to work the gate without supervision."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>174</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I attacked him. I'm here alone."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>175</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Him? The Chimaera." Some kind of understanding appears on his face. "He's been around a *long* time, son. Not so easy to get rid of as all that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>176</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The resonance chamber has been smashed. I need to know how to fix it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>177</ID>
      <DefaultText>He puts a hand to his chin, all anger and suspicion gone in the face of a puzzle. "Well, it ain't that hard if you know the basics. The chamber's crystal, yeah? So it's grown, not built. So long as the chamber's core is intact, it should know how to grow itself. You just need a catalyst to..."

He trails off and looks at you anew. "*Why* do you want to know this? The resonance chamber's only good for..." He gives you an angry look. "Who sent you? Why are you after this?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>178</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm trying to stop the Sorrow from hunting us."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>179</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Specter - a, uh... being... in my head. He told me if I fix it I could stop the Sorrow from hunting us down."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>180</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't worry about that. Just answer the question."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>181</ID>
      <DefaultText>Mazzof barks a short, bitter laugh. "I don't doubt it would stop the Sorrow, and a great many other things. I don't know how, but the Changing God's trying to use you. If that chamber's fixed, nobody benefits but him. You can't trust a damn word that bastard says."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>182</ID>
      <DefaultText>Mazzof barks a short, bitter laugh. "I don't doubt it would stop the Sorrow, and a great many other things. The Changing God's trying to use you. If that chamber's fixed, nobody benefits but him. You can't trust a damn word that bastard says."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>183</ID>
      <DefaultText>Mazzof glowers. "I'm not telling you a damn thing. The only person who benefits from the chamber is the Changing God, and I ain't helping *him* anymore. He'll just destroy us all."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>184</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why would the Changing God lie to me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>185</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It wasn't the Changing God who told me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>186</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How would the resonance chamber benefit the Changing God?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>187</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What does the resonance chamber do?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>188</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ha! Well, if it that's true then it's someone who only has our sire's interests in mind. Stay away is my advice."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>189</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why do you think?" Mazzof hitches up his ragged breeches. "Why does he do anything? To get what *he* wants."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>190</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Our sire has a new castoff body that he plans to use as a catalyst for the chamber, but the First has a better plan - something that *won't* snuff out every last one of us. Look for her in... in the Bloom," he says grimly. "Just make sure you don't -"

Before he can finish, you feel a wrenching twist in the center of your body like your heart is being wrung dry. Your vision tunnels black, and you feel as though your body were being sucked through a steel pipe. You're being pulled out of the Mere, but it's far more painful than it ever was before.

Then Mazzof, the cave, and everything else disappears.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>191</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Chimaera's shifting voice cuts through your conversation. "Hold on!" He shoves you aside and presses the metal tendrils, shutting the portal to Mazzof immediately. "Tell me now, *where* is this resonance chamber? It's vital that we - "

Before he can finish, you feel a wrenching twist in the center of your body. Your vision tunnels black, and you feel as though your body were being sucked through a steel pipe. The Chimaera, the cave, and everything else disappears.

{SOUND: Mere ending sound.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>194</ID>
      <DefaultText>When you first open your eyes, there's only a ruddy glow and frightening shapes in shadows around you. The air is hot and stifling.

As your eyes adjust, you realize you're outside, but the sky is darkened by clouds of pitch. The ruddy glow comes from lava flows as they trundle down distant mountains into the volcanic fields all around you.

Sharp towers pierce the sky, tapered like the bones of a rib cage. Indeed, they look like bones in every way, as does the ground beneath you. You appear to be standing on the spine of an enormous beast - the bottom of its jaw can be seen far in the distance, half-buried beneath a layer of cooled lava.

{ART: The Spine}
{SOUND: Volcanic rumblings (should this be a constant ambient sound?)}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>195</ID>
      <DefaultText>Most of the bone towers look identical, but one shines from the inside with an odd, blue light. The top of the glowing tower has been snapped off, and what looks like a transport hovers next to its peak. It's *your* transport. You were sent here to find something...

Twisted bridges connect the spine to the volcanic fields around you. In one direction lie enormous formations of obsidian: arches, spires, a wall. In the other direction a narrow pass is carved into the mountain face. The field leading to the canyon is illuminated by hundreds of glowing lights.

You know this body wasn't sent to find Mazzof, but Aadiriis said he'd appear. Perhaps following through events will lead to him.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>196</ID>
      <DefaultText>You find a staff made of some prior world metal. It's cool to the touch - unusual given the extreme temperature of the air itself - and burn marks blacken one end.

Very likely, this was used as a weapon. It may work again, but probably only once. You take the staff with you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>199</ID>
      <DefaultText>Attack the Chimaera with the staff.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>200</ID>
      <DefaultText>You aim the charred end of the staff at the Chimaera's back and press the button on the side. A thunderclap booms in the cavern and a scalding beam of light strikes the Chimaera between his shoulders. He shouts and falls onto the table.

Suddenly you are blinded by a bright flash of light. You shield your eyes, preparing for a counterattack, but none comes. When you can see again, the Chimaera is gone.

{SOUND: Lightning Lance.}
{SOUND: Flashbang as Chimaera disappears.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>201</ID>
      <DefaultText>With the Chimaera gone you investigate the cage. The moment you step near it, a glowing hand with three fingers appears on the side of the one of the metal tendrils. It disappears when you place your hand on it and is replaced by a ring of small circles.

When you look at each circle, a different image appears in your mind of a person or a place. You look at each circle again and again until a memory stirs and you know which one is Mazzof.

Pressing that circle activates the cage, and you step inside.

{SOUND: Open portal sound}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>202</ID>
      <DefaultText>Another event occurred here. The fire wights have killed many people over hundreds - even thousands - of years. These deaths culminated in the creation of something called a gemorrn, a creature of pure rage. The gemorrn has since wandered these volcanic fields with an insatiable lust for revenge, mostly against the wights that created it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>203</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>204</ID>
      <DefaultText>Taunt the gemorrn from a distance. Get it to chase you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>205</ID>
      <DefaultText>Taunt the gemorrn again to get it to chase you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>206</ID>
      <DefaultText>Reaching into the earth, you find the body called Ama and summon her forth. With uncanny strength, she crawls out from the cooled rock. Though her skin is charred and rotting, a castoff tattoo is clearly visible on her head.

You command her to collect the sphere. The wights are preoccupied with the gemorrn, and so Ama's body reaches the sphere easily and returns it to you. Then the corpse collapses.

{SOUND: "Had a memory" stinger or use ability sound}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>207</ID>
      <DefaultText>With the wights ignoring you, searching the fields is relatively easy. You find a kind of shield embedded in the molten rock, and you *feel* rather than see the strong presence of death here.

Searching further, you find a copper sphere lying on the ground.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>208</ID>
      <DefaultText>You are on the volcanic plains in front of the mountain pass. The gemorrn and the fire wights are still fighting a terrible battle. The wights have surrounded the gemorrn now. They seem intent on destroying it. But the creature is very strong and cornered. It could be a long fight.

{SOUND: Gemorrn and wights fighting}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>209</ID>
      <DefaultText>Get the shield.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>210</ID>
      <DefaultText>The wights don't bother you as you try to pry the shield from the ground, but after a few minutes of tugging and digging you realize it's impossible. The rock has cooled and melted and cooled again several times around the device. It's not going anywhere.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>211</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>212</ID>
      <DefaultText>You watch the wights, avoiding their attention and circling the plain for a long time.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>213</ID>
      <DefaultText>You find a shield embedded in the rock, and you can *feel* the strong presence of death in that spot.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>214</ID>
      <DefaultText>You see a copper sphere, though the wights consistently cut off any paths to it, preventing you from getting near it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>215</ID>
      <DefaultText>But you can make no sense of their behavior.

They are obviously interested in protecting the sphere for some reason, but otherwise they seem to be milling about aimlessly except when you antagonize them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>216</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>217</ID>
      <DefaultText>You watch the wights, avoiding their attention and circling the plain for a long time.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>218</ID>
      <DefaultText>You find a shield embedded in the rock, and you can *feel* the strong presence of death in that spot.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>219</ID>
      <DefaultText>You see a copper sphere, though the wights consistently cut off any paths to it, preventing you from getting near it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>220</ID>
      <DefaultText>But you can make no sense of their behavior. They seem to be milling about aimlessly.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>221</ID>
      <DefaultText>Attack them with the staff again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>222</ID>
      <DefaultText>They flinch back as you raise the staff again. You press the button on the side... nothing happens.

Fortunately the wights don't seem to have noticed that your weapon only had one shot - not yet, anyway.

{SOUND: Ineffective weapon click}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>223</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Who are you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>224</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What happened to you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>225</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why can't I speak with the girl?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>226</ID>
      <DefaultText>Let her return to her peace.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>227</ID>
      <DefaultText>Ama becomes silent. You sense a wave of gratitude and annoyance, but mostly the former. Then nothing. Her presence is gone. You feel like no asking will bring her back.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>228</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ama?" The disembodied voice sounds like it's calling Ama rather than naming herself. "No, not Ama. Shelled. Cast away. Eaten and alive and eaten again. Not Ama. Food for wights."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>229</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Buried to death. Before that, lived. Before that, died. Before that, lived and died and lived and... So many cycles. So many deaths."

The air shivers. Her tone drops dangerously low. "Before that, someone else. Awoke and remembered. A fight. A girl. Urlimnion."

Though you cannot see Ama, her presence moves through you, turns your head. You see in the fields, in the distance, what she is talking about. The urlimnion. A sphere of burnished metal lying in the rock. And you *know* this is what you were sent here to find.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>230</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Gone. Gone, but not gone." You shudder, but it's not you who is shuddering. "She woke something. Vengeance. Though no vengeance is in her."

You feel Ama's presence looking off toward the obsidian formations. There's something glowing - and *moving* - over there.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>231</ID>
      <DefaultText>Unfortunately, the Wights only interest now is you. They quickly decide you're not going to attack them again. Several of them rush toward you at once.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>232</ID>
      <DefaultText>The air grows colder as the wights close in. You bolt in the opposite direction. They stay on your tail all the way to the bridge and onto the spine itself.

So you duck into the glowing tower heading toward the transport. As soon as you enter the tower, the air grows warm again. The wights will not enter the tower. After a while, they leave, returning the fields they came from.

{SOUND: Zerian running}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>233</ID>
      <DefaultText>The only body on the surface is the corpse you called forth. You can feel other dead beneath the rock, preserved by magma that has flowed over this spot over the centuries.

The corpse is a middle-aged woman named Ama. The dead beneath is a girl, but she is strangely silent. Even with your strange powers, there is nothing there to speak with.

"Peace," says Ama. "Is it better? Better, yes. Better oblivion."

{SOUND: "Had a memory" stinger or use ability sound}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>234</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Buried to death. Before that, lived. Before that, died. Before that, lived and died and lived and... So many cycles. So many deaths."

The air shivers. Her tone drops dangerously low. "Before that, someone else. Awoke and remembered. A fight. A girl. Urlimnion."

Though Ama's corpse doesn't move, her presence ripples through you. She speaks of the sphere you tried to get her to retrieve for you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>235</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>236</ID>
      <DefaultText>

It's the gemorrn, a pillar of light with claws. A hundred faces twist in its body - emerging, howling, then melting back into the curling fire. The creature is easily three meters wide, and at least twice as tall.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>237</ID>
      <DefaultText>

It's like a pillar of light with claws. A hundred faces twist in its body - emerging, howling, then melting back into the curling fire. The creature is easily three meters wide, and at least twice as tall. The word "gemorrn" bubbles to your mind.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>238</ID>
      <DefaultText>

Several of its faces turn toward you. They open their mouths in unison, and their scream is like the sound of a hundred people being torn apart by broken hounds. The impact of its rage strikes you like a hurricane.

{ART: Gemorrn}
{SOUND: Gemorrn roar}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>239</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Buried to death. Before that, lived. Before that, died. Before that, lived and died and lived and... So many cycles. So many deaths."

The air shivers. Her tone drops dangerously low. "Before that, someone else. Awoke and remembered. A fight. A girl. Urlimnion."

Though Ama's corpse doesn't move, her presence ripples through you. You realize she's speaking about the sphere she collected for you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>240</ID>
      <DefaultText>Enter the transport anyway.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>241</ID>
      <DefaultText>Don't board the ship just yet.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>242</ID>
      <DefaultText>You back away from the transport. The nagging worry disappears immediately, as though it were only a brief hallucination.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>244</ID>
      <DefaultText>You take two steps toward the cage, but the moment you reach your hand toward it, the Chimaera stops you with a bark. "What do you think you're doing? Your mission is a failure. The last thing I want is to have you out there making more trouble for me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>245</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>246</ID>
      <DefaultText>

DEBUG INFO:
Timer Variable = [Global: MB1_TimerVariable]
TimerVariableLimit = [Global: MB1_TimerVariable_TooLong]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>247</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>248</ID>
      <DefaultText>Draw your whip and attack the gemorrn.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>249</ID>
      <DefaultText>Whip the gemorrn again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>250</ID>
      <DefaultText>You lash your whip at the gemorrn. It has as much effect as whipping a campfire.

{SOUND: Whip}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>251</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The resonance chamber's only good for one thing." He holds up a finger. "And that's snuffing us out. The Changing God plans to use it to merge all of us - every castoff that still lives - back into his body. *That's* his plan for stopping the Sorrow."

He puts a grease-stained hand on your shoulder. "Look. I don't know who you are, or what your part in this is, but you *cannot* let him activate that chamber. You need..." He glances over your shoulder at something in the cavern, though when you turn, you see nothing there.

"The First is *alive*," he whispers, drawing your attention back to him. "And she's got her own plan for the chamber, one that won't kill us all."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>252</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>253</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine the cage to figure out how it works.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>254</ID>
      <DefaultText>Ignore him. Examine the cage again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>255</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Chimaera grabs your arm with a grip like steel. "No."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>256</ID>
      <DefaultText>A dozen different eyes narrow with suspicion. "No," he says finally. "I cannot allow that. Go rest, pending further instructions."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>260</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm not really Zerian. I'm a new castoff, using a Merecaster to project myself. I was told you could fix the resonance chamber."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>261</ID>
      <DefaultText>Mazzof's human eye grows as wide as a saucer. His other eye flips through a few images, landing on a red eye with three pupils that scrutinizes you up and down. "This is beyond me, and that's saying something," he says. "About the resonance chamber though, the only one who benefits from it is the Changing God. That bastard's got nobody's interests at heart but his own. Don't listen to a damn thing he says."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>262</ID>
      <DefaultText>Perhaps Zerian's mission will aid you on your own.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>263</ID>
      <DefaultText>Perhaps Zerian's mission will aid you on your own.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>264</ID>
      <DefaultText>Perhaps Zerian's mission will aid you on your own.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>265</ID>
      <DefaultText>Perhaps Zerian's mission will aid you on your own.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>266</ID>
      <DefaultText>[DEBUG] Skip to the end.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>267</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>268</ID>
      <DefaultText>Use your connection to the dead to animate a corpse and have the corpse get the sphere for you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>269</ID>
      <DefaultText>Try animating a corpse to get the sphere for you again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>270</ID>
      <DefaultText>Again, Ama's body crawls out from the cooled rock, and again the wights devour her life force. It looks like you'll need something more to get past the wights.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>271</ID>
      <DefaultText>Perhaps that copper sphere is what you were sent here to find.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>272</ID>
      <DefaultText>It seemed like they were fighting over the copper sphere. Perhaps that's what you were sent here to find.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>273</ID>
      <DefaultText>It looked like they were fighting over the copper sphere. Perhaps that's what you were sent here to find.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>274</ID>
      <DefaultText>That copper sphere *must* be what you were sent here to find.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>275</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>276</ID>
      <DefaultText>Using the temperature of the air to feel where their attention might be, you close the distance to the sphere by about a hundred meters. The wights don't seem to notice you.

{SlipPastWightsCounter = [Global: MB1_SlipPastWightsCounter]
WightIsFollowing = [Global: MB1_WightIsFollowingPC]}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>277</ID>
      <DefaultText>You close the distance by another hundred meters. The wights still don't notice you.

{SlipPastWightsCounter = [Global: MB1_SlipPastWightsCounter]
WightIsFollowing = [Global: MB1_WightIsFollowingPC]}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
